This paper proposes a solution to Neural Architecture Search (NAS) using stochastic optimization and differentiable loss functions. The paper focuses on experiments with image classification datasets, indicating a likely connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses reinforcement learning-based NAS, suggesting a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses experiments with natural language processing (NLP) datasets, indicating a possible connection to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
